      • convertToFileURI

        public static java.net.URI convertToFileURI(java.lang.String path)
        Convert the given path to an absolute URI. If the given path represents something on the local file system, then the path will be converted to a full absolute path and converted to a file: URI, if not then it will be returned verbatim.
        Parameters:
        path - the path to convert
        Returns:
        the URI of the path
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if path is empty
